  "response": "The concept of a truly \"bottomless pit\" is impossible, as all physical objects have a finite depth. However, if we consider a hypothetical deep pit with no bottom, here's what would happen:\n\n1. In reality, you would not die from falling indefinitely\n2. Instead, you would continue falling at a constant velocity due to air resistance\n3. Terminal velocity for a human body is around 120 mph (193 km/h)\n4. You would experience continuous weightlessness\n5. Eventually, other factors like oxygen supply or exposure would become life-threatening\n\nIn a practical scenario with a very deep pit:\n- Death would likely occur from:\n  - Lack of oxygen\n  - Extreme cold\n  - Psychological stress\n  - Eventual impact if the pit has an end\n\nThe time to death would depend on the specific conditions of the pit, but could range from hours to days.\n\nThis is a theoretical scenario, as no actual bottomless pit exists in reality.",
